('LA Memorial Coliseum', '3911 S. Figueroa Street, Los Angeles, CA 90037', 'http://www.lacoliseum.com/', 'outdoor', 'The Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum is an American sports stadium located in the Exposition Park neighborhood of Los Angeles, California. The stadium serves as the home to the University of Southern California (USC) Trojans football team, and as the temporary home for the Los Angeles Rams of the National Football League (NFL).', 'http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3069/2488767697_6f162f1087_b.jpg'),
('MetLife Stadium', '50 State Highway 120, East Rutherford, NJ 07073', 'http://www.metlifestadium.com/', 'outdoor', 'MetLife Stadium is an American sports stadium located in East Rutherford, New Jersey. It is part of the Meadowlands Sports Complex and serves as the home stadium for two National Football League (NFL) franchises: the New York Jets and the New York Giants.', 'http://www.adweek.com/wp-content/uploads/files/news_article/fea-crupi-stadiums-hed-2012.jpg'),
('FedEx Field', 'FedEx Field, Landover, MD 20785-4236', 'http://www.redskins.com/fedexfield/', 'outdoor', 'FedExField is a football stadium located in Landover, Maryland near the Capital Beltway in Prince George''s County, Maryland, United States, near the site of the old Capital Centre. FedExField is the home of the Washington Redskins football team.', 'http://www.nbaspirit.fr/photos/1627493.jpg?PHPSESSID=f47ee18cdb4785c84c64a5ceb334d5c3'),
('Lambeau Field', '1265 Lombardi Avenue, Green Bay, WI 54304', 'http://www.packers.com/', 'outdoor', 'Lambeau Field is an outdoor athletic stadium in the north central United States, located in Green Bay, Wisconsin. The home field of the Green Bay Packers of the National Football League (NFL), it was named in August 1965 in memory of Packers founder, player, and long-time head coach, Curly Lambeau, who had died two months earlier.', 'http://prod.static.packers.clubs.nfl.com/assets/images/lambeau-field/lambeau--field-2000.jpg'),
('AT&T Stadium', '925 N Collins St, Arlington, TX', 'http://attstadium.com/', 'Retractable Roof', 'AT&T Stadium, formerly Cowboys Stadium, is a retractable roof stadium in Arlington, Texas, United States. It serves as the home of the Dallas Cowboys of the National Football League (NFL) and was completed on May 27, 2009. It is also the home of the Cotton Bowl Classic.', 'http://kswo.images.worldnow.com/images/12505806_G.jpg'),
('Arrowhead Stadium', 'One Arrowhead Drive, Kansas City, MO', 'http://www.chiefs.com/arrowhead/', 'Outdoor', 'Arrowhead Stadium is a football stadium in Kansas City, Missouri, United States, that primarily serves as the home venue of the Kansas City Chiefs of the National Football League.', 'http://football.ballparks.com/NFL/KansasCityChiefs/aerial.jpg'),
('Mile High Stadium', '1701 Bryant Street, Denver, CO', 'http://www.sportsauthorityfieldatmilehigh.com/', 'Outdoor', 'Sports Authority Field at Mile High, previously known as Invesco Field at Mile High, and commonly known as Mile High or Mile High Stadium, is an American football stadium in Denver, Colorado.', 'https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/originals/ab/5c/46/ab5c4674c35221b9d1bb8cdd0e47fe13.jpg'),
('Bank of America Stadium', '800 South Mint Street, Charlotte, NC 28202', 'http://www.panthers.com/stadium/', 'Outdoor', 'Bank of America Stadium is a 75,419-seat football stadium located on 33 acres in uptown Charlotte, North Carolina, United States. It is the home facility and headquarters of the Carolina Panthers of the National Football League.', 'https://dilemmaxdotnet.files.wordpress.com/2012/01/bank-of-america-stadium.jpg'),
('Ralph Wilson Stadium', '1 Bills Dr., Orchard Park, NY 14127-2237', 'http://www.buffalobills.com/stadium/', 'Outdoor', 'New Era Field, originally Rich Stadium and formerly known as Ralph Wilson Stadium, is a stadium in Orchard Park, New York, a suburb south of Buffalo. Opened in 1973, it is the home of the Buffalo Bills of the National Football League.', 'http://image.newyorkupstate.com/home/nyup-media/width620/img/photo-gallery/photo/2015/05/13/17784583-mmmain.jpg'),
('Mercedes-Benz Stadium', 'Atlanta, GA', 'http://mercedesbenzstadium.com/', 'Retractabel Roof', 'Mercedes-Benz Stadium is a multi-purpose retractable roof stadium under construction in Atlanta, Georgia that will serve as the home of Atlanta United FC of Major League Soccer and the Atlanta Falcons of the National Football League.', 'http://prod.static.falcons.clubs.nfl.com/assets/images/imported/ATL/photos/clubimages/2015/08-August/tempMBStadium-City-Plaza--nfl_mezz_1280_1024.jpg'),
('Mercedes-Benz Superdome', '1500 Sugar Bowl Drive, New Orleans, LA 70112', 'http://www.mbsuperdome.com/', 'Indoor', 'The Mercedes-Benz Superdome, often referred to simply as the Superdome, is a domed sports and exhibition venue located in the Central Business District of New Orleans, Louisiana, United States. It primarily serves as the home venue for the New Orleans Saints of the National Football League (NFL), and is also the home stadium for the Sugar Bowl and New Orleans Bowl in college football.', 'https://media1.britannica.com/eb-media/81/94981-004-4CF726AB.jpg'),
('FirstEnergy Stadium', '1085 West 3rd Street, Cleveland, OH 44114', 'http://www.clevelandbrowns.com/stadium/fe-stadium.html', 'Outdoor', 'FirstEnergy Stadium, officially FirstEnergy Stadium, Home of the Cleveland Browns, is a multi-purpose stadium in Cleveland, Ohio, United States, primarily for American football.', 'https://www.theclio.com/web/ul/25060.55019.jpg'),
('NRG Stadium', 'One Reliant Park, Houston, TX 77054', 'https://www.nrgpark.com/nrg-park-facilities/nrg-stadium/', 'Retractabel Roof', 'NRG Stadium, formerly Reliant Stadium, is a multi-purpose stadium, in Houston, Texas, United States. NRG Stadium has a seating capacity of 71,795, a total area of 1,900,000 square feet with a 97,000 sq ft playing surface', 'https://i.gse.io/gse_media/116/4/1463085286-nrg-stadium-tickets.jpg?p=1'),
('M&T Bank Stadium', '1101 Russell St., Baltimore, MD 21230', 'http://www.baltimoreravens.com/gameday/mt-bank-stadium.html', 'Outdoor', 'M&T Bank Stadium is a multi-purpose football stadium located in Baltimore, Maryland. It is the home of the Baltimore Ravens of the National Football League.', 'https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/originals/46/41/63/464163a9ef9a77b281d90ada5897c352.jpg'),
('Lincoln Financial Field', '1020 Pattison Avenue, Philadelphia, PA, 19148', 'http://www.lincolnfinancialfield.com/', 'Outdoor', 'Lincoln Financial Field is the home stadium of the National Football League''s Philadelphia Eagles and the Temple Owls football team of Temple University. It has a seating capacity of 69,176.', 'https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/31/Le_Lincoln_Financial_Field.jpg'),
('Nissan Stadium', 'One Titans Way, Nashville, TN 37213', 'http://www.titansonline.com/stadium/', 'Outdoor', 'Nissan Stadium is a multi-purpose stadium in Nashville, Tennessee, United States, owned by the Metropolitan Government of Nashville and Davidson County.', 'https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/originals/2b/08/33/2b083373b26a665b2e7469a2c2c61cfd.jpg'),
('Levi''s Stadium', '4900 Marie P. DeBartolo Way, Santa Clara, CA 95054', 'http://www.levisstadium.com/', 'Outdoor', 'Levi''s Stadium is a football stadium located in Santa Clara, California, in the San Francisco Bay Area. It has served as the home of the San Francisco 49ers of the National Football League since 2014.', 'http://assets.internationalchampionscup.com/uploads/photo/file/25/large_lev-1429638984.jpg'),
('EverBank Field', 'One EverBank Field Drive, Jacksonville, FL 32202', 'http://www.jaguars.com/everbank-field/', 'Outdoor', 'EverBank Field is an American football stadium in Downtown Jacksonville, Florida, and the home stadium facility of the Jacksonville Jaguars of the National Football League.', 'http://www.stadiumsofprofootball.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/ever16_bottom.jpg'),
('U.S. Bank Stadium', '401 Chicago Ave, Minneapolis, MN 55415', 'https://www.usbankstadium.com/', 'Indoor', 'U.S. Bank Stadium is a fixed-roof stadium located in the Downtown East section of Minneapolis, Minnesota, United States, on the former site of Hubert H. Humphrey Metrodome.', 'http://www.vikings.com/assets/images/imported/MIN/photos/clubimages/2016/06-June/tempaerials-060216-2-006--nfl_mezz_1280_1024.jpg'),
('Rayond James Stadium', '4201 N Dale Mabry Hwy, Tampa, FL 33607', 'http://raymondjamesstadium.com/', 'Retractabel Roof', 'Raymond James Stadium, also known as the "Ray Jay", is a multi-purpose football stadium located in Tampa, Florida. It is home to the Tampa Bay Buccaneers of the National Football League as well as the NCAA''s South Florida Bulls football team.', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/y2vHeYeCEQQ/maxresdefault.jpg'),
('Paul Brown Stadium', '1 Paul Brown Stadium, Cincinnati, OH 45202-3418', 'http://www.bengals.com/stadium/', 'Outdoor', 'Paul Brown Stadium is an outdoor football stadium in the north central United States, located in Cincinnati, Ohio. It is the home venue of the Cincinnati Bengals of the National Football League and opened on August 19, 2000.', 'http://football.ballparks.com/NFL/CincinnatiBengals/newaerial.jpg'),
('Hard Rock Stadium', '2269 N.W. 199th St., Miami, FL 33056', 'http://hardrockstadium.com/', 'Outdoor', 'Hard Rock Stadium is a multipurpose football stadium located in Miami Gardens, Florida, a suburb north of Miami. It is the home stadium of the Miami Dolphins of the National Football League, and the Miami Hurricanes from the University of Miami.', 'http://19053-presscdn-0-53.pagely.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/canopy3-3.jpg'),
('Heinz Field', '100 Art Rooney Avenue, Pittsburgh, PA 15212', 'http://heinzfield.com/', 'Outdoor', 'Heinz Field is a stadium located in the North Shore neighborhood of Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, United States. It primarily serves as the home to the Pittsburgh Steelers of the National Football League (NFL) and the Pittsburgh Panthers of the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA). The stadium opened in 2001, after the controlled implosion of the teams'' previous stadium, Three Rivers Stadium.', 'https://i.gse.io/gse_media/116/8/1473279298-heinz-field-tickets.jpg?p=1'),
('Ford Field', '2000 Brush Street, Detroit, MI 48226', 'http://www.fordfield.com/', 'Retractabel Roof', 'Ford Field is a multi-purpose indoor stadium located in Downtown Detroit, Michigan, United States, owned by the Detroit/Wayne County Stadium Authority. It is primarily used for American football as the home field of the Detroit Lions of the National Football League (NFL) as well as the annual Quick Lane Bowl college football bowl game.', 'https://www.gannett-cdn.com/-mm-/b8684aeb01c1291dd6abd4fc8bd8e9b55451aadc/c=6-0-3727-2798&r=x408&c=540x405/local/-/media/2016/08/17/DetroitFreePress/DetroitFreePress/636070396268982506-Ford-Field-Completed-AG-Roof-Restoration-July-31-2016-1.jpg'),
('Soldier Field', '425 East McFetridge Drive, Chicago, IL', 'https://soldierfield.net/', 'Outdoor', 'Soldier Field is an American football stadium located in the Near South Side of Chicago, Illinois. It opened in 1924 and is the home field of the Chicago Bears of the National Football League, who moved there in 1971.', 'http://www.cz-studio.com/_i/SOLDIER_02.jpg'),
('Lucas Oil Stadium', '500 South Capitol Avenue, Indianapolis, IN 46225', 'http://www.lucasoilstadium.com/', 'Retractabel Roof', 'Lucas Oil Stadium is a multi-purpose stadium in downtown Indianapolis, United States. It replaced the RCA Dome as the home field of the NFL''s Indianapolis Colts. The stadium also hosted Super Bowl XLVI in 2012.', 'http://68.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lyzuw3mdpt1qjza6po1_1280.jpg'),
('University of Phoenix Stadium', '1 Cardinals Drive, Glendale, AZ, 85305', 'http://www.universityofphoenixstadium.com/', 'Retractabel Roof', 'University of Phoenix Stadium is a multi-purpose football stadium located in Glendale, Arizona, west of Phoenix. It is the home of the Arizona Cardinals of the National Football League and the annual Fiesta Bowl.', 'https://res.cloudinary.com/simpleview/image/upload/crm/phoenix/58801_9171_UofP-Stadium-with-Great-Lawn-View_b8c57ff9-5056-b3a8-4994ce8f703ae694.jpg'),
('Los Angeles Stadium at Hollywood Park', 'Inglewood, CA 90305', 'http://www.hollywoodparklife.com/', 'Outdoor', 'The Los Angeles Stadium at Hollywood Park is a sports and entertainment district under construction in Inglewood, California, United States. It will be located approximately 3 miles from Los Angeles International Airport and adjacent to The Forum.', 'http://www.fieldofschemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/la-sp-nfl-stadium-renderings-pg-012.jpg'),
('CenturyLink Field', '800 Occidental Ave S, Seattle, WA 98134', 'http://www.centurylinkfield.com/', 'Outdoor', 'CenturyLink Field is a multi-purpose stadium located in Seattle, Washington, United States. It is the home field for the Seattle Seahawks of the National Football League (NFL) and Seattle Sounders FC of Major League Soccer (MLS).', 'http://www.ase.org/sites/ase.org/files/Centuruy-Link--Wiki-Commons-.jpg'),
('Las Vegas Stadium', '800 Occidental Ave S, Seattle, WA 98134', 'http://lasvegasstadium.raiders.com/?gclid=CM-cyoXupNQCFYOEswodlfkHag', 'Indoor', 'Las Vegas Stadium is the working name for a domed stadium planned to be built in Paradise, Nevada for the Las Vegas Raiders of the National Football League (NFL) and the UNLV Rebels football team from the University of Nevada, Las Vegas (UNLV).', 'http://static4.businessinsider.com/image/57c08bb909d29325008b4bb4-1190-625/here-is-the-gorgeous-2-billion-stadium-the-las-vegas-raiders-are-expected-to-call-home.jpg'),
('Gillette Stadium', '1 Patriot Pl, Foxborough, MA 02035', 'http://www.gillettestadium.com/', 'Outdoor', 'Gillette Stadium is a stadium located in Foxborough, Massachusetts, 24 miles southwest of downtown Boston and 20 miles northeast of downtown Providence, Rhode Island.', 'http://images.patriots.com/20160420-gs-new-1.jpg'),
('Oriole Park', '333 West Camden Street, Baltimore, MD 21201', 'http://baltimore.orioles.mlb.com/bal/ballpark/', 'Outdoor', 'Oriole Park at Camden Yards, often referred to simply as Camden Yards or Oriole Park, is a Major League Baseball ballpark located in Baltimore, Maryland.', 'https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/KwTlw724syfLBvnYMtmeH1p5J80=/0x0:4246x2831/1200x800/filters:focal(0x0:4246x2831)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/46988246/GettyImages-474735050.0.jpg'),
('Fenway Park', '4 Yawkey Way, Boston, MA 02215', 'http://boston.redsox.mlb.com/bos/ballpark/', 'Outdoor', 'Fenway Park is a baseball park located in Boston, at 4 Yawkey Way near Kenmore Square. Since 1912, it has been the home for the Boston Red Sox, the city''s American League baseball team, and since 1953, its only Major League Baseball franchise.', 'http://www.ballparksofbaseball.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/fenway_topv3.jpg'),
('Guaranteed Rate Field', '333 West 35th Street, Chicago, IL 60616', 'http://mlb.mlb.com/cws/ballpark/index.jsp', 'Outdoor', 'Guaranteed Rate Field is a baseball park located in Chicago, Illinois that serves as the home ballpark for the Chicago White Sox, a Major League Baseball club competing in the American League Central division.', 'https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/s--0yW62VCm--/c_scale,fl_progressive,q_80,w_800/nnpq9lnwwwtbnzidz1si.jpg'),
('Progressive Field', '2401 Ontario Street, Cleveland, OH 44115', 'http://cleveland.indians.mlb.com/cle/ballpark/', 'Outdoor', 'Progressive Field is a baseball park located in the downtown area of Cleveland, Ohio, United States. It is the home field of the Cleveland Indians of Major League Baseball and, together with Quicken Loans Arena, is part of the Gateway Sports and Entertainment Complex.', 'http://assets.westincleveland.com/lps/assets/u/ProgressiveField-1.jpg'),
('Comerica Park', '2100 Woodward Avenue, Detroit, MI 48201', 'http://detroit.tigers.mlb.com/det/ballpark/', 'Outdoor', 'Comerica Park is an open-air ballpark located in Downtown Detroit. It serves as the home of the Detroit Tigers of Major League Baseball, replacing Tiger Stadium in 2000.', 'https://c1.staticflickr.com/7/6119/6269490113_3d9de23b00_b.jpg'),
('Minute Maid Park', '501 Crawford Street, Houston, TX 77002', 'http://houston.astros.mlb.com/hou/ballpark/', 'Retractable Roof', 'Minute Maid Park, previously known as The Ballpark at Union Station, Enron Field, and Astros Field, is a ballpark in Downtown Houston, Texas, United States, that opened in 2000 to house the Houston Astros of Major League Baseball.', 'http://www.ballparksofbaseball.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/minute_topv3.jpg'),
('Kauffman Stadium', 'One Royal Way, Kansas City, MO 64129', 'http://kansascity.royals.mlb.com/kc/ballpark/', 'Outdoor', 'Kauffman Stadium, often called "The K", is a baseball park located in Kansas City, Missouri, that is home to the Kansas City Royals Major League Baseball team.', 'http://www.ballparksofbaseball.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/kauff09951.jpg'),
('Angel Stadium', '2000 Gene Autry Way, Anaheim, CA 92806', 'http://kansascity.royals.mlb.com/kc/ballpark/', 'Outdoor', 'Angel Stadium of Anaheim, originally known as Anaheim Stadium and later Edison International Field of Anaheim, is a modern-style ballpark located in Anaheim, California.', 'https://i.gse.io/gse_media/114/6/1406569210-venue-AngelsStadium_Intr_Day.jpg?p=1'),
('Target Field', '1 Twins Way, Minneapolis, MN 55403', 'http://minnesota.twins.mlb.com/min/ballpark/', 'Outdoor', 'Target Field is a baseball park located in the historic warehouse district of downtown Minneapolis. It is the home ballpark of the Minnesota Twins, the state''s Major League Baseball franchise.', 'http://thefan1230.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Target-Field.jpg'),
('Yankee Stadium', 'One East 161st Street, Bronx, NY 10451', 'http://newyork.yankees.mlb.com/nyy/ballpark/', 'Outdoor', 'Yankee Stadium is a stadium located in the Concourse section of the Bronx, a borough of New York City. It serves as the home ballpark for the New York Yankees of Major League Baseball. ', 'http://m.mlb.com/assets/images/9/8/6/176398986/cuts/20150721_STADIUM_AGH_1131_2000x1333_nkhmtv84_4wh74k09.jpg'),
('Oakland Coliseum', '7000 Coliseum Way, Oakland, CA 94621', 'http://www.coliseum.com/', 'Outdoor', 'The Oaklandâ€“Alameda County Coliseum, often referred to as the Oakland Coliseum, is a multi-purpose stadium in Oakland, California, United States, which is home to both the Oakland Athletics of Major League Baseball (MLB) and the Oakland Raiders of the National Football League (NFL). ', 'http://www.ballparksofbaseball.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/oco_topv2.jpg');

